items.title: Donaldson hits 2 homers, one going 481 feet
items.summary: Josh Donaldson's homer-heavy second half continued in a big way on Sunday.

items.title: Waino poised to return in relief role
items.summary: After receiving high marks for his work during a simulated inning on Sunday morning, Adam Wainwright appears ready to return from the 10-day disabled list for the Cardinals' series opener against the Reds on Tuesday. And when he does, it will be as a reliever.

items.title: Betts exits, day to day with thumb injury
items.summary: Mookie Betts exited with a right thumb contusion in the fifth inning of Sunday's game with the Rays. He is listed as day to day, the team announced.
